Text.string: A rare antlered spiderant! I must have it on my credenza. Kill it!
Well done, Vault Hunter. Well done indeed! I shall hang Mercenary Day decorations from those antlers!
Beware the Manvark! Additionally, kill the Manvark!
And so the Manvark's reign of terror is over... for now.
Why is this rakk known as “The Phoenix”? Fell it, Vault Hunter, and find out.
And so The Phoenix fell, and then rose! And then fell again! And then rose a third time! And now it's dead. Your persistence, Vault Hunter, has paid off.
Legend speaks of the blood-drinking Chupacabratch! End its sanguine feast!
The good farmers and monks can now live without fear, for the Chupacabratch is slain. Bloody good kill, Vault Hunter.
Show me what you're made of and take out that Big Foot monster!
Show me what you're made of and take out that Chonk Stomp monster.
The mightiest of saurians was he! But like a mighty tree, you have felled the beast and brought it to an end. I am most thrilled to have this beast upon my wall!
Beware the Jabbermogwai, Vault Hunter! And don't let it get wet!
Well struck, Vault Hunter! Calloo, callay, etcetera, etcetera.
The Blinding Banshee! It screams! It blinds! It hates you personally! There you are, three good reasons to kill it!
The Blinding Banshee was the terror of the mythical Nekrotafeyo, and yet there you are, slaying legends themselves! Huzzah!
Egad! Exterminate that swarm of creepy critters, Vault Hunter!
Well struck! You could say they were... hopping mad. Hohohoho!
There's a creepy crawly creature squirming about near you. Hunt it down for me!
What a disgusting and fascinating specimen. It will look marvelous atop my mantle. Well done, Vault Hunter!

Greetings, Vault Hunter! I am Sir Hammerlock, and I require you to hunt and kill things for me! You see, the Borderlands are full of rare and dangerous specimens. I will pay you top dollar for their trophies!
Lavender Crawly is the matriarch of the Crawly family, a bloodline of particularly snooty varkids. She must die!
Good show! But I imagine that's not the last we've seen of the Crawly family. At least, I certainly hope not.
That airborne abomination is known as a “skrakk”! Correct nature's mistake and kill it for me!
Good show! The only place for the skrakk in all of creation is on my wall of monstrosities!
